## Step 2 — Check Railway Variables are named correctly

In Railway → **cei-recruiting-api** → **Variables** tab, it must show:

| Name (left column) | Value (right column) |
|---|---|
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | `AIzaSyDh6...` |
| `FRONTEND_URL` | `https://cei-recruiting-frontend-4nn8.vercel.app` |
| `PORT` | `3001` |

From the screenshot I saw the values were there but the **variable names** may be missing — Railway needs the name on the left, value on the right.

---

## Step 3 — Get Railway URL

Once build succeeds (green ✓), click **cei-recruiting-api** → **Settings** → **Networking** → **Generate Domain** → copy URL

Then open that URL + `/health` in browser — should show `{"status":"ok"}`

---

## Step 4 — Add to Vercel

Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables → add/update:
```
VITE_API_URL = https://your-railway-url.railway.app
